As I got exposed for the first time to individual Rocket Parts, I got familiarized with the software and jargon... 
Now it's time to see the big picture of Rocket Design.
These are the families for LRE I've classified so far;

1. Propellant feed components --> bring oxidizer and fuel to the engine. https://ntrs.nasa.gov/api/citations/20100035254/downloads/20100035254.pdf
    Fuel inlet
    Oxidizer inlet
    Feed line
    Manifold
    Propellant distribution passage
    Valve body
    Valve seat
    Valve poppet / pintle / spool depending on valve style
    Filter / screen
    Flange / line interface
    Tubing fittings / couplers

2. Injector System --> Atomizes and Streamlines the propellant into the Combustion Chamber of the TCA.
    Injector plate
    Injector element
    Injector orifice
    Fuel passage
    Oxidizer passage
    Swirl chamber if swirl injector
    Tangential inlet slot if swirl injector
    Coaxial post if coaxial injector
    Injector face
    Injector cup / element recess depending on design
    Baffle if injector stability hardware is present
    Acoustic cavity / resonator in some designs


3. Combustion Chamber Sytem --> Pressure vessel and heat-transfer battlefield.
    Combustion chamber liner
    Chamber jacket
    Chamber wall
    Thrust chamber assembly (TCA)
    Igniter port boss
    Igniter mount
    Sensor port
    Pressure tap boss
    Injector mounting flange
    Chamber closeout
    Structural shell

4. Throat and Nozzle System --> Hot gas gets expanded into thrust
    Throat section
    Converging section
    Diverging nozzle
    Nozzle wall
    Nozzle extension
    Nozzle skirt
    Exit flange
    Nozzle reinforcement ring
    Film cooling ring / slot if present


5. Cooling System --> 
    Cooling channel
    Coolant inlet manifold
    Coolant outlet manifold
    Channel rib / land
    Channel closeout
    Regenerative cooling jacket
    Film cooling passage
    Dump cooling passage if applicable


6. Ignition System -->
    Igniter
    Igniter body
    Igniter port
    Spark plug or torch igniter depending on architecture
    Igniter injector
    Igniter mount bracket / boss


7. Structural and Interface Hardware -->
    Mounting flange
    Engine mount interface
    Bracket
    Support ring
    Stiffener
    Clamp
    Bolt pattern interface
    Retainer
    Pin
    Clevis
    Gimbal interface if gimbaled
    Actuator bracket if TVC is present


8. Sealing and Joining Hardware -->
    Seal groove
    O-ring gland
    Gasket interface
    Weld joint
    Brazed joint
    Threaded interface
    Face seal surface


9. Turbomachinery compoentns -->
    Pump impeller
    Inducer
    Volute
    Pump casing
    Turbine wheel
    Turbine housing
    Shaft
    Bearing housing
    Seal housing
    Turbine nozzle guide vane
    Turbopump inlet
    Turbopump discharge


10. Control / Actuation components -->
    TVC actuator
    Rod-end clevis
    Clevis bracket
    Pivot pin
    Gimbal ring
    Gimbal mount
    Actuator linkage


Approximating about 40-100 Parts within these sections total!

